&lt;p&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp; has a higher precedence than =, so in the second if, you are assigning the value of &lt;code&gt;fn1(1) &amp;amp;&amp;amp; $var4 == 123&lt;/code&gt; (true or false) to $var2.&lt;/p&gt;

